DBT-Style Terraria Mod – Full Concept Notes

1. Game Progression & Form Unlocks

Start of Game

Hidden Trait Roll: one random trait per player; stored internally, bonuses inactive.

Debug item exists (for testing only).

No forms available.

After Eye of Cthulhu

Buff: “Mysterious Power” appears (generic aura icon).

Tooltip: "You feel a strange energy within you… but its nature is unclear."

Early ki use limited to base skills.

After Skeletron

Elder Kai Quest unlocks: Unlock Potential

Complete sparring challenge to reveal trait and unlock Potential Unleashed.

Ki bar recolored, bonuses now active.

Form mastery XP begins.

Hardmode Start (Wall of Flesh)

SSJ1 unlocked via quest or rage mechanic.

Trait affects mastery gain:

Prodigy: faster mastery progression.

Legendary: higher damage, more ki drain.

Post-Mechanical Bosses

SSJ2 unlock.

Optional SS God side-quest (requires rare drop/NPC trigger).

Post-Plantera

SS God or Legendary SSJ3 depending on trait.

Trait paths diverge (Prodigy → God/Blue; Legendary → SSJ3/SSJ4).

Post-Golem / Pre-Moon Lord

SSB unlock (Prodigy path).

SSJ4 quest unlock (open to all traits except Prodigy, requires special item).

Post-Moon Lord / Late Game

Ultra Instinct, Ultra Ego, SSJ4 Full Power, SSJ4 Limit Breaker.

Zeno/Grand Priest optional event for trait reroll, hints, or form unlock assistance.

2. Traits & Gameplay Effects
Trait	Theme	Effects	Ki Bar Color
Legendary	Raw, uncontrollable power	×2 Max Ki, +25% SSJ damage, +30% ki drain. Cannot use God/Blue/Rose. Gains SSJ3 & SSJ4 earlier.	Green-gold
Prodigy	Mastery & refinement	Mastery XP ×2, -15% ki drain, +5% crit. Cannot use Legendary SSJ. Gains God → Blue earlier.	Blue-silver
Warrior’s Spirit	Balanced	+15% damage & defense, normal ki regen, no form locks	Red-orange
Battle Genius	Tactical	+10% crit, +20% ki regen <50% HP, +10% mastery gain	Purple-silver
Iron Will	Endurance	-25% ki drain, -20% mastery gain, +10 defense	Steel gray
Draconic	Fiery offense	Melee/ki attacks inflict On Fire!, +15% ki damage, -15% ki regen	Fiery red-gold
Corrupted/Evil	Dark power	Unlocks SS Rose path; blocked from Beerus/Whis mentorship	Black-purple
Optional debug item for rerolling traits.

3. NPC Mentors & Dialogue

Elder Kai (Pre-Hardmode)

Unlocks Potential Unleashed and early mastery.

Dialogue per trait:

Legendary: “Hmm, your energy is fierce and wild… control it or be consumed.”

Prodigy: “Ah, your spirit is sharp… master forms faster than most.”

Warrior’s Spirit: “Balanced warrior… strength comes from patience.”

Battle Genius: “You fight with cunning… combine wit with power.”

Iron Will: “Endurance is remarkable… focus is key.”

Draconic: “A fierce fire burns within you… use wisely.”
Beerus (Hardmode Mentor)

Unlocks God-related forms after trials.

Refuses evil trait characters.

Dialogue per trait:

Legendary: “Control your chaos or be consumed.”

Prodigy: “Quick learner… worthy of divine training.”

Warrior’s Spirit: “Steady and strong… don’t falter.”

Battle Genius: “Brains and brawn… dangerous combo.”

Iron Will: “Endurance is useful… handle true power.”

Draconic: “Your flames may burn bright… don’t burn alive.”

Whis (Post-Beerus Approval)

Unlocks God Ki forms: SSG → SSB → Ultra Instinct.

Provides mastery guidance and hints.

Dialogue per trait:

Legendary: “Harness raw power carefully… fine line between strength and self-destruction.”

Prodigy: “Eager to master forms… serves you well.”

Warrior’s Spirit: “Balance and patience… virtues bring harmony.”

Battle Genius: “Sharp mind and technique… continue refining both.”

Iron Will: “Stamina supports training… focus energy.”

Draconic: “Fiery nature… gift and challenge. Temper it with discipline.”
Zeno / Grand Priest (Optional Late Game)

Can grant:

Trait reroll

Hint for next form unlock

Inner power boost

Requires achievement milestone (e.g., post-Moon Lord).

